  zipper manifest
  
  <file>: Define a file entry in the generated ZIP archive file
  
    path        - Destination path within the generated archive
    source      - Location of the source file on the local file system
    normalize   - (Optional) Flag indicating if the source file line endings should be normalized: "none|windows|unix" (default:none)
    
 <directory>: Define a directory entry in the generated ZIP archive file
   
    path        - Destination path within the generated archive (default:root)
    source      - Location of the source directory on the local file system
    filter      - (Optional) file inclusion filter (default:*.*)
    recursive   - (Optional) flag to include the directory recursively (default:true)

  Example:
  
  <zip>
    <file source="D:\absolute\myfile.bin" path="path\to\file"/>
    <file source="..\relative\myfile.txt" path="path\to\file" normalize="unix"/>
    <directory source="..\mycode" path="mycode" filter="*.c" recursive="true"/>
  </zip>
